# Cloudflare cache rules.
#
# Lesson learned: NEVER put `immutable` on a file whose name doesn't change
# when its contents change. `immutable` tells the browser to never revalidate
# — so an edited home.css / hero3d.js keeps serving the stale cached copy
# (you can't even hard-refresh it away on iOS Safari). Instead we revalidate:
# the browser sends a conditional request, Cloudflare returns a tiny 304 when
# nothing changed, and the moment a file changes the browser picks it up.
# Bandwidth is unmetered on Cloudflare, so the revalidation round-trips are free.

# Everything: revalidate every load (ETag → 304 when unchanged) + security headers.
/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

# Images and the 3D model rarely change — let them sit briefly to cut
# round-trips, but NO `immutable`, so they still self-heal within the hour.
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/models/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600
